Anti-aging research fits under the broader category of biomedical research.
See for instance [this GiveWell post](http://blog.givewell.org/2014/01/15/returns-to-life-sciences-funding/).

Some places to begin looking:

- [Wikipedia's page on it](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_extension)

- [Aubrey de Grey](https://www.quora.com/Aubrey-de-Grey) on Quora, and SENS

- [Evan Gaensbauer's comment](http://effective-altruism.com/ea/7m/open_thread/hs)

- [Fight Aging!](https://www.fightaging.org/), and other websites like it

- João Pedro de Magalhães' paper: [The Scientific Quest for Lasting Youth: Prospects for Curing Aging](http://pcwww.liv.ac.uk/~aging/rr14_curing_aging_prospects.pdf)
